.html|archive-date=16 July 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* [[File:Roundel of the USAF.svg|24px|USAF Roundel]] United States Navy \u2013 8 September 2004: [[CH-46 Sea Knight|CH-46E Sea Knight]] 153372 Shot down by RPG Fire South of Camp Fallujah, crashes and is burned out near Al-Buaisa. All four crew members injured.<ref name=\"thirdseries3\">{{cite web|last1=Baugher|first1=Joe|url=http://www.joebaugher.com/navy_serials/thirdseries19.html|title=US Navy and US Marine Corps BuNos-Third Series (150139 to 156169)|publisher=Joe Baugher|accessdate=20 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.af.mil/news/story_print.asp?storyID=123008770 |title=Airmen help save lives following UH-60 crash at Tallil |author=Master Sgt. Don Perrien |publisher=Air Force Print News |date=27 September 2004 |accessdate=11 February 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20120718112018/http://www.af.mil/news/story_print.asp?storyID=123008770 |archivedate=18 July 2012 }}</ref>\n* [[File:Roundel of the USAF.svg|24px|USAF Roundel]] United States Army Aviation \u2013 9 November 2004: US OH-58D Kiowa shot down by rocket fire over Fallujah.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.theage.com.au/news/Iraq/US-helicopter-shot-down-over-Falluja/|title=US Helicopter Shot Down Over Falluja|work=The Age |date=November 2004}}{{dead link|date=February 2017|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref>\n* [[File:Roundel of the USAF.svg|24px|USAF Roundel]] [[United States Marine Corps]] \u2013 11 November 2004: AH-1W SuperCobra 161021 from [[HMLA-169]] is shot down by RPG and small arms fire near Fallujah. It is destroyed by Iraqi rebel forces, crew recovered intact.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://homepage.ntlworld.com/nigel.sadler1/Accidents_2004.htm |title=Naval Air Accidents 2004 |accessdate=2 June 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080613073313/http://homepage.ntlworld.com/nigel.sadler1/Accidents_2004.htm |archivedate=13 June 2008 }}</ref>\n* [[File:Roundel of the USAF.svg|24px|U